text:
"You mustn't get wrapped up in the past at your time of life;
      plenty of that when you get to my age. That's a nice dress -- I
      like the style."

Again Soames nodded. "I must be getting back to her," he said;
      "she just wanted to know for certain. We may have to take steps. I
      suppose there's no mistake?"

"Of course Soames is a connoisseur," Aunt Juley said hastily;
      "he has wonderful taste -- he can always tell beforehand what's
      going to be successful."

"Built on sand," answered Jolyon, pressing her hand hard;
      "but it's a pleasure to do anything, at any time, remember
      that. And if you change your mind...! Come along, June; say good-bye."

Val's head jerked on its stem. It was like a blow between the eyes,
      so utterly unthought of, so extreme and ugly in the midst of his dreaming;
      and he looked at Holly with eyes grown suddenly, touchingly haggard.

"No. I've been shadowed for a long time; one gets used to
      that. But then Soames came. By the little Niobe -- the same story;
      would I go back to him?"

"It'll be a scandal," muttered James, as if to himself;
      "but I can't help that. Don't brush so hard. When'll
      it come on?"

"Well," said Winifred, "if they were in London, perhaps;
      in London it's amusing to do nothing. But out there, of course, he'll
      simply get bored to death."
